{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ad191261-1684-4b31-813c-7a0e4d43aa44","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. None of the available skills cover dump **analysis** (only collection), but here's how to proceed:\n\n### Recommended tool: `dotnet-dump analyze`\n\nInstall and launch it against your dump:\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze <path-to-your.dmp>\n```\n\n### Key commands once inside the analyzer:\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (or `printexception`) | Print the last exception |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a specific thread |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview (for OOM issues) |\n| `eestack` | All managed thread stacks |\n\n### Typical workflow:\n1. Run `pe` — if there's an unhandled exception, this shows the type, message, and stack trace immediately.\n2. Run `clrthreads` — look for threads with exceptions (marked in the Exception column).\n3. Use `setthread` + `clrstack` to inspect suspicious threads.\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start an interactive analysis session with your dump file? If so, please share the path to the `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ced30751-c0b6-4567-b480-5cca900ddd15","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **configuring and collecting** crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\" So that skill isn't appropriate here.\n\nThere's also `dotnet-trace-collect` which is for capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps.\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing crash dumps. Let me provide guidance directly.\n\n\nFor analyzing the dump, the main tools available are `dotnet-dump analyze` which works cross-platform, or `lldb` with the SOS plugin on Linux/macOS, and WinDbg with SOS on Windows. Since we're likely on Linux, I'll guide them through using `dotnet-dump analyze` or `lldb` to examine the crash dump and identify what caused the failure.","outputTokens":635,"requestId":"DA01:1287AC:724590E:7AFC13B:6A03DA5E"},"id":"c77e316b-ab7e-4bd4-b261-d63e000a3811","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:57:01.630Z","parentId":"32b7dcfc-f785-4b05-b24b-11b150c04b8c"}
